did.unittitle: Edward Tripp, editor of the Yale University Press, records

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of lists, correspondence, manuscript materials, and committee notes documenting the publication of various works by the Yale University Press. Some of the works documented include: Interaction of Color by Josef Albers, Encyclopedia of African Studies by John M. D. Crossey, and Earth, Temple, and Gods and Shingle Style by Vincent Scully.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 34-A (YRG 34-A), Administrative records of the Yale University Press.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the records is restricted. See Collection Contents for details.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Edward Tripp, Editor of the Yale University Press, Records (RU 323). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged alphabetically by authors' last names and by subject.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of lists, correspondence, manuscript materials, and committee notes documenting the publication of various works by the Yale University Press. Some of the works documented include: Interaction of Color by Josef Albers, Encyclopedia of African Studies by John M. D. Crossey, and Earth, Temple, and Gods and Shingle Style by Vincent Scully.
